The paper deals with the use of deep learning techniques for automatic image captioning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of temporal consistency constraints to create summaries of image streams, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the captioning algorithms for image retrieval, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
